explanation: This solution uses the find method to locate the index of the character ch in the string word. If the character is not found, it returns the original string. Otherwise, it splits the string into two parts: the prefix and the suffix. It then reverses the prefix and concatenates it with the suffix to form the result. The time complexity is O(n) because the find method and the concatenation operations take linear time. The space complexity is also O(n) because in the worst case, the prefix and suffix can be of the same size as the original string.

